# Mirror docs (mrp_pipeline)

This repo is part of a multi-root workspace with the **Notes** knowledge base.
MRP supply-planning strategy notes mirror into `docs/supply-planning/` here.

## Current state

- **Canonical (edit here in Notes):** `Notes/projects/mrp/supply-planning/` — six files (hub README + five strategy notes).
- **Mirrors (generated):** `docs/supply-planning/` in this repo — synced by `scripts/sync_project_docs.py` from Notes.
- **Application doc:** `Project_Documentation.md` (project-canonical, not mirrored).

## Where to edit

| Content | Edit in |
|---------|---------|
| Application architecture | This repo: `Project_Documentation.md` |
| Layer 0-1 supply-planning strategy | **Notes** `projects/mrp/supply-planning/` |
| Reusable meta/math theory | **Notes** `meta/`, `math/` |

## Keeping mirrors in sync

After editing any canonical file under `Notes/projects/mrp/supply-planning/`:

```bash
# from Notes repo root
py scripts/sync_project_docs.py --write
py scripts/sync_project_docs.py --check
```

Then commit regenerated mirrors in this repo. CI (`.github/workflows/mirror-check.yml`) runs `--check` on PRs touching `docs/supply-planning/**`.

## Never edit mirror files directly

Mirrors carry a `MIRROR:` banner and are regenerated from Notes.

